# Hurricane Data Analysis

## Project Overview
This project analyzes historical hurricane data, categorizing storms by mortality, damage, and affected areas. It also generates visualizations using Matplotlib and Seaborn to provide insights into the most devastating hurricanes.

## Features
- Data cleaning and processing
- Categorization by mortality and damage
- Analysis of most affected areas
- Visualizations for key insights

## Installation
1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/hurricane-analysis.git
   cd hurricane-analysis
   ```
2. Install dependencies:
   ```bash
   pip install -r requirements.txt
   ```

## Running the Script
Run the script using:
```bash
python hurricane_analysis.py
```

## Visualizations
The script generates bar charts for:
- Most affected areas
- Deadliest hurricanes
- Most costly hurricanes

